meta {
  name: 13 Import Lab Tests into Branch
  type: http
  seq: 14
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/branch-lab-tests/import
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{operatorToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "labTestIds": ["{{labTestId}}"]
  }
}

docs {
  **Prerequisite 3a — Import the lab test into the active branch's list.**

  Deep-copies the master-data lab test into the branch's Lab Test List as an
  independent branch-owned snapshot (with a fresh id + `sourceLabTestId`
  provenance). Tenant + active branch come from the operator's JWT — which is why
  this runs under `operatorToken`. Returns `{ copied, skipped }` (re-importing an
  already-present test is idempotently skipped).

  The new `branchLabTestId` is not in this response — step 15 resolves it.
}
